        <div class="poem-field" id="poem1">
            <h2 class="poem-title">When I Was Four</h2>
            <h5 class="poem-author">by Vera Didenko</h5>
    <br>
    <br>
            <p class="poem-body">
                When I was four I was told 
                <br>That if I draw a lot,
                <br>I could become a wonderful artist.
                <br>What an interesting thought.
                <br>
                <br>
                <br>Indeed I always wished to draw
                <br>Amazing so that when anyone saw
                <br>My pictures would think they are real.
                <br>But what if they decide to steal
                <br>My masterpiece indeed?
                <br>For one would certainly inside
                <br>Fill with jealosy and greed.
                <br>But no, who could ever
                <br>In the whole wide world decide
                <br>To be so mean to a child
                <br>Just so meek and mild.
                <br>
                <br>
                <br>Siting and thinking on my bed,
                <br>I started to draw a horse’s head.
                <br>Trying my best, trying all day,
                <br>I drew a horse on a log 
                <br>And seeing it my mom did say:
                <br>“What a wonderful dog!”
                <br>
                <br>
                <br>Suddenly, the picture that I just started to admire,
                <br>The horse that I to draw as a photo did desire
                <br>Made me feel that ofcourse!
                <br>I drew a dog not a horse!
                <br>I still need to practice a lot
                <br>If I want to become an artist I thought.
                <br>
                <br>
            </p>
